19:
I guess no matter what I say, we
won't understand each other.
22: I can tell you're hungry though.
25: Say, do you know what cats eat?
40:
Mikoto, huh. What's a little girl like
you doing out here alone?
49: O-oh! Sorry, I didn't mean to assume.
52:
It's just... I've never seen clothes like
that before. Where are you from?
56: If I said prison, would you believe me?
64:
I'm kidding. I've been cooped up in a
hospital nearby and got bored
enough to escape.
67: What's your name, by the way?
75: Ayumu, hm? That's a nice name.
98:
That should be my line, y'know. You
gave me a heart attack back there.
101:
I see you're still making the same
weird noises when you cry.
105:
Did you... Did you get your memories
back?!
109:
Yep. I remember you, Mom, Dad...
Everyone.
112: I'm sorry it took me so long.
117:
Weh... WAAHHEUUUGH! You should
be sorry!
120:
The way you cry seriously kills the
mood...
125:
A good brother wouldn't be making
his sister cry in the first place.
134:
Indeed. She's the one who brought
you here, as Stella and the others
are still in the other world.
136:
Without her abilities, I'm not sure we
would've found you. You should be
thanking her.
140:
There's no need. I owe you a great
debt, so I will always come to your
aid if needed.
150:
A word, if you don't mind? I
apologize for bothering you so soon
after waking, but this is urgent.
159:
The connection started to break
while we were pulling you out. It took
us an entire day to repair the
damage.
163:
...The cause was most likely your
sister.
166:
But I can't say for certain. There's
also the possibility that things
would've been much worse if it had
been anyone else.
174:
He wasn't able to cross the Rift, and
considering the risks involved, we
weren't about to force him.
178:
So that means... We won't be able to
bring the others from Shibuya over
either.
181:
Something is off about that world of
yours... if we can even call it a world.
It's suspended in the Rift somehow...
183:
You know, when the connection was
breaking down, Stella reported that
it only lasted a few moments on her
end. Do you realize what that means?
186:
The difference in the flow of time
between here and there is in the
tens of thousands.
193:
So there's... probably nothing left
outside Shibuya either...
198:
Even with the Antipode Lance, could
we save the people stranded in
Shibuya?
201:
I can't make any promises, but it's
the only chance we have.
209:
Planning on leaving your sister all by
her lonesome again? You're a
terrible brother.
214:
Just so you know, she had me
watching over you the whole time
you were asleep. She kept insisting
that you would disappear at any
moment.
218:
Sorry to be a bother... Could you
keep an eye on her for me?
222: Promise to return, and I will.
226: Of course. I promise I'll come back.
231:
You really should learn to act more
in your own interests.
234:
Unlike the situation with us Vesta,
you can prioritize your own people
without worrying about others for
once.
238:
You say that like I haven't just been
acting on my whims this whole time.
241:
It's why I still have so much left to do.
My focus keeps switching from one
whim to the next.
245:
Say what you will. I know the
truth—you are kind to a fault.
249: I'm not so sure about that.
253:
Maybe one day I'll manage to be the
kind person you see me as. But for
now, it's a work in progress.
260:
I agree with Memram on this
one—you're stubborn and kind to a
fault.
278:
Let's go, Stella. It's time to pry some
answers out of Sakuya Hoshino.
